// D1.0 net-expansion: INT_MIN % -1 — AGREEMENT pin (not a divergence).
// Interpreter returns 0 (ops.rs divisor==-1 special case). Cranelift's srem
// legalization also returns 0 for the overflow pair, so the backends agree
// today — unlike sdiv, which overflow-traps (see t_intmin_div_neg1, marked).
// This pin locks the agreement so drift on either side trips PARITY_FAIL.
a: t8 = -128
b: t8 = -1
print(a % b)
